# meimberg.io Contentmanager

## Storyblok Rate Limits

Storyblok Management API has rate limits (~5 requests/second).

**When making bulk updates:**
- Add 200ms delay between requests: `await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 200))`
- Implement retry with exponential backoff for rate limit errors
- Check for "Rate limit" in error messages

**Example pattern:**
```typescript
let delay = 200
for (const item of items) {
  if (index > 0) await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, delay))
  try {
    await updatePost(id, data)
  } catch (err) {
    if (err.message?.includes('Rate limit')) {
      delay *= 2 // exponential backoff
      // retry...
    }
  }
}
```

## Blog Content Model

- Blog posts are stored in Storyblok `/blog` folder with `blog` component
- Content complete requires ALL 9 fields: pagetitle, pageintro, teasertitle, abstract, teaserimage, readmoretext, date, headerpicture, body
- Publish state uses Storyblok native publish/unpublish (not a custom field)
- Source material (source_raw, source_summarized) comes from Plaud email import
